            $redirect_uri = &#39;https://&#39; . $_SERVER[&#39;HTTP_HOST&#39;] . $_SERVER[&#39;PHP_SELF&#39;];
            $client-&gt;setRedirectUri($redirect_uri);
            $auth_url = $client-&gt;createAuthUrl();

            // Actually GO to the authentication (and authorization) url
            header(&#39;Location: &#39; . filter_var($auth_url, FILTER_SANITIZE_URL));
        }
    }

At first, the webpage redirects us to google where we need to grant access for our application to the desired email to send messages with. Once approved, a token file is created that we store in a file. When the token expires, a new token should be created automatically with `fetchAccessTokenWithRefreshToken()` - [more here](https://www.oauth.com/oauth2-servers/access-tokens/access-token-lifetime/).

