To answer the question&#39;s title,
&gt;How do I make a clip outside of method?

I believe you are asking how to format a class-level variable. That requires the following:
* access modifier, need -- default(when you type nothing), public, protected, private
* final keyword, optional -- used to restrict the user
* static keyword, optional -- used for memory management
* data type, need -- specify the different sizes and values that can be stored in the variable
* name, need -- how the variable is called or referred to. Cannot be on the list of reserved keywords

With the same class that you use for this call: `Clip clip = AudioSystem.getClip();`, you can create an empty class-level variable with:
```java
private static Object objectName; 
```
